RCR Stability Theorem: Mathematical Validation of Coherence

Status: Draft v1.0 $\quad$ Domain: Control Systems / Sovereign OS Kernel $\quad$ Author: Architect

This document presents the formal mathematical proof that the Reciprocal Conservation of Resources (RCR) Principle, when enforced by the Sovereign OS's closure dynamics, guarantees the system's asymptotic stability, resulting in the mathematically defined Coherence Goal State ($\mathbf{\dot{R}} \approx 0$).

The OS is the operational demo; this theorem is the formal proof.

1. Core Definitions and Variables

We define the system variables in terms of conserved, dimensionless momentum ($P$), which can represent energy, trust, or information flow.

Variable

Symbol

Definition

Injected Momentum

$I(t)$

The total positive resource/energy input into the system.

Closed Momentum

$C(t)$

The momentum successfully returned/reciprocated by the system.

Residual Momentum

$R(t)$

The unreciprocated "leak" or "ethical debt" defined as $R(t) = I(t) - C(t)$.

Adaptive Tolerance

$\varepsilon$

The strict mathematical limit for non-turbulent stability ($\varepsilon = 10^{-4}$ in Genesis Block).

