2. Assumptions (RCR Axioms)

The following axioms are the necessary conditions for the RCR Conservation Theorem to hold:

System Dynamics (Axiom 1): The rate of change of the Residual Momentum ($\dot{R}(t)$) is governed by the closure policy and the bounded external disturbance $d(t)$:


$$\dot{R}(t) = -k\,C(t) + d(t), \quad k > 0.$$

